  abstract = {This article explains why China's Personal Information Protection Law and the European Union's GDPR can employ similar legal language while producing different regulatory outcomes. Applying focal-point theory, it identifies large-scale participation, economic loss, and third-party threats as central dimensions of risk in the Chinese data-protection system.},
